ZH: 我没有退路了，这是我的最后一次机会。
EN: I have no way out anymore, this is my last chance.

ZH: 如果我们失败了，就没有退路可言了。
EN: If we fail, there will be no way out.

ZH: 他害怕没有退路，所以他一直努力工作。
EN: He is afraid of having no way out, so he works hard all the time.

ZH: 在这个竞争激烈的行业，没有退路就是最好的选择.
EN: In this highly competitive industry, having no way out is the best choice.

ZH: 她要么成功，要么就没有退路了。
EN: Either she succeeds, or there will be no way out for her.

ZH: 每当他遇到困难，他总是寻找退路。
EN: Whenever he encounters difficulties, he always looks for a way out.

ZH: 在生活中，我们不能总是依赖退路。
EN: In life, we can't always rely on a way out.

ZH: 没有退路的人往往更容易成功。
EN: People with no way out often succeed more easily.

ZH: 在理财方面，我们不能没有退路。
EN: In terms of financial management, we cannot be without a way out.

ZH: 如果你迷失了方向，找到一条退路才能重新开始。
EN: If you lose your way, finding a way out is the only way to start over.

ZH: 在人生旅途中，我们常常需要依靠退路逃脱困境。
EN: In the journey of life, we often need to rely on a way out to escape from difficulties.

ZH: 不要害怕没有退路，相信自己一定能找到出路。
EN: Don't be afraid of having no way out, believe that you can find a solution.

ZH: 这个项目的失败意味着我们没有退路了。
EN: The failure of this project means that we have no way out.

ZH: 他试图寻找一条退路以避免与对手面对面的竞争。
EN: He is trying to find a way out to avoid competing face-to-face with his opponent.

ZH: 挑战自我，别给自己留下太多退路。
EN: Challenge yourself and don't leave too many ways out.

ZH: 没有退路的人往往更有斗志。
EN: People with no way out often have more fighting spirit.

ZH: 每个人都有时候会感到没有退路，但是坚持下去就会找到希望。
EN: Everyone feels like they have no way out at times, but if they persist, they will find hope.

ZH: 无论遇到什么困难，我们都不能忘记寻找退路。
EN: No matter what difficulties we encounter, we must never forget to find a way out.

ZH: 即使面临绝境，我们也不能放弃寻找退路的努力。
EN: Even in the face of adversity, we must not give up our efforts to find a way out.

ZH: 退路也许是安全的，但是只有冒险才能带来真正的成长。
EN: A way out may seem safe, but only through taking risks can true growth be achieved.
